  <source>University of Zurich</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      With the new software tool (EDI, enhanced depth imaging) of the Spectralis® spectral-domain
      optical coherence tomography (SD-OCT) it is possible to visualize and measure the choroidal
      thickness. In glaucoma a vascular component is known. Therefore a difference of choroidal
      thickness in glaucoma patients and healthy controls is proposed.

        -  Trial with medical device
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
